The article is a transcript of remarks made by Vice President Mike Pence during a groundbreaking ceremony for a new auto parts manufacturing plant in Lancaster, Ohio. Pence praised the strong economy and job growth under the Trump administration, highlighting the creation of 6 million new jobs since 2016. He also emphasized the importance of the United States-Mexico-Canada Agreement (USMCA) and urged Congress to pass it, stating that the agreement would create more jobs and investment in the automotive industry. Pence called on the audience to contact their elected officials and voice their support for the USMCA. He also paid tribute to a local soldier who had recently died in Afghanistan.